write me apoem about headace and spring, make it short

In spring's gentle embrace, the flowers bloom,  
Yet in my temple dwells an aching gloom.  
Soft winds carry whispers through the meadow,  
But within, a pulse beats strong and slow.

The sun paints colors on the morning sky,  
While in my mind, dull drumming won't subside.  
Petals dance gently, in the cool, crisp air,  
As I seek solace from this nagging wear.

Though spring renews the world with vibrant grace,  
My heavy head seeks peace in a quiet place.  
In nature's beauty, I find tender relief,  
A breath of calm amidst my burdened grief.
